HEADWORD: Flotson
<hw>Flot"son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>flotter</ets> to float. See
<er>FFlotilla</er>, and cf. <er>Jetsam</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>Goods lost by shipwreck, and floating on the sea; -- in distinction
from <xex>jetsam</xex> or <xex>jetson</xex>.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
